00:21:57.286 --> 00:21:59.056 A:middle
So now let's talk
about the actions

00:21:59.456 --> 00:22:01.576 A:middle
that the user can take
on the notifications.

00:21:59.456 --> 00:22:01.576 A:middle
that the user can take
on the notifications.

00:22:02.546 --> 00:22:04.006 A:middle
There are three types of actions

00:22:04.246 --> 00:22:06.536 A:middle
that your applications
can be aware of.

00:22:08.756 --> 00:22:11.036 A:middle
The first one is
the default action.

00:22:11.686 --> 00:22:14.756 A:middle
It is when the user opens
your app from a notification.

00:22:16.176 --> 00:22:18.486 A:middle
This can be done when
the device is unlocked

00:22:18.486 --> 00:22:21.206 A:middle
and the user receives a
notification, they can tap

00:22:21.246 --> 00:22:23.486 A:middle
on the banner, which
will open your app.

00:22:24.416 --> 00:22:27.716 A:middle
It can also be done from the
lock screen when the user swipes

00:22:27.776 --> 00:22:32.436 A:middle
from left to right, as well
as in the Notification Center

00:22:32.836 --> 00:22:35.736 A:middle
when the user swipes down to
present the Notification Center,

00:22:36.156 --> 00:22:38.126 A:middle
they can tap on any
of your notification

00:22:38.526 --> 00:22:39.526 A:middle
to open your application.

00:22:42.436 --> 00:22:44.936 A:middle
Now the second type of
actions are custom actions.

00:22:45.446 --> 00:22:47.676 A:middle
And they are within the
actionable notifications.

00:22:48.386 --> 00:22:51.356 A:middle
We introduced actionable
notifications in iOS 8

00:22:52.186 --> 00:22:53.796 A:middle
and they provide
the user a quick way

00:22:53.796 --> 00:22:57.066 A:middle
to execute an action
directly from the notification

00:22:57.656 --> 00:22:59.766 A:middle
without the need of
launching your app.

00:23:01.416 --> 00:23:04.296 A:middle
Now these custom actions,
they appear as buttons

00:23:04.396 --> 00:23:07.316 A:middle
with customizable title below
the notification content.

00:23:09.126 --> 00:23:12.556 A:middle
In iOS 9 we introduced
text input actions

00:23:12.976 --> 00:23:16.286 A:middle
so that the user can for example
quickly reply to a message

00:23:16.936 --> 00:23:18.716 A:middle
of directly from
the notification.

00:23:19.246 --> 00:23:25.606 A:middle
And these custom actions can be
either background or foreground.

00:23:26.056 --> 00:23:28.976 A:middle
A background action will
dismiss the notification

00:23:29.426 --> 00:23:31.726 A:middle
and give you a short amount
of time in the background

00:23:31.836 --> 00:23:34.506 A:middle
to process that custom action
that the user selected.

00:23:35.546 --> 00:23:38.756 A:middle
On the other hand, a foreground
action will dismiss the

00:23:38.756 --> 00:23:41.976 A:middle
notification and launch your
application in the foreground

00:23:41.976 --> 00:23:43.676 A:middle
so that you can process
that custom action.

00:23:46.266 --> 00:23:47.996 A:middle
Now these custom
actions are available

00:23:47.996 --> 00:23:50.056 A:middle
on both iOS and watchOS.

00:23:52.036 --> 00:23:55.346 A:middle
So first, let's take a look
at what it looks like on iOS.

00:23:56.796 --> 00:23:59.086 A:middle
Here we have an example
of an iPhone 6S.

00:23:59.816 --> 00:24:02.506 A:middle
On this device, the
user can use 3D touch

00:23:59.816 --> 00:24:02.506 A:middle
On this device, the
user can use 3D touch

00:24:02.896 --> 00:24:04.166 A:middle
to expand a notification.

00:24:05.496 --> 00:24:08.776 A:middle
When they do so the custom
actions will appear below the

00:24:08.776 --> 00:24:09.836 A:middle
notification content.

00:24:09.836 --> 00:24:11.526 A:middle
And some of these actions,

00:24:11.526 --> 00:24:13.326 A:middle
as you can see can
be text input actions

00:24:13.666 --> 00:24:19.276 A:middle
so the user can quickly
reply to a message.

00:24:19.426 --> 00:24:23.316 A:middle
Now on watchOS, same
thing, the custom actions,

00:24:23.716 --> 00:24:25.656 A:middle
appear below the
notification content,

00:24:26.216 --> 00:24:30.176 A:middle
and some of these actions can
also be text input actions.

00:24:30.726 --> 00:24:32.856 A:middle
And on the watchOS, you
have the opportunity

00:24:32.856 --> 00:24:36.356 A:middle
to provide some suggestions that
the user is likely to choose

00:24:37.106 --> 00:24:38.266 A:middle
for your text input action.

00:24:40.076 --> 00:24:42.726 A:middle
Now for more information
about notifications

00:24:42.726 --> 00:24:46.366 A:middle
on watchOS you can attend the
Quick Interaction Techniques

00:24:46.366 --> 00:24:50.866 A:middle
for watchOS Session later today.

00:24:51.046 --> 00:24:51.866 A:middle
So now that we've talked

00:24:51.866 --> 00:24:54.406 A:middle
about what the custom
actions look like.

00:24:54.796 --> 00:24:57.536 A:middle
Let's first talk about how you
can register your custom actions

00:24:57.786 --> 00:24:59.366 A:middle
and then present
them to the user.

00:24:59.956 --> 00:25:05.016 A:middle
So for registration, the first
thing you will need to do is

00:24:59.956 --> 00:25:05.016 A:middle
So for registration, the first
thing you will need to do is

00:25:05.016 --> 00:25:06.326 A:middle
to create an action object.

00:25:06.976 --> 00:25:09.966 A:middle
You give it a unique
identifier, as well as a title.

00:25:10.676 --> 00:25:13.036 A:middle
The title will appear on
the customizable buttons

00:25:13.036 --> 00:25:15.826 A:middle
that we previously saw.

00:25:15.966 --> 00:25:18.276 A:middle
Action will be by
default background action,

00:25:18.816 --> 00:25:21.016 A:middle
but you can also provide some
option such as if you want it

00:25:21.016 --> 00:25:24.026 A:middle
to be a foreground action.

00:25:24.146 --> 00:25:25.756 A:middle
Now, all your actions they need

00:25:25.756 --> 00:25:27.646 A:middle
to be associated
with categories.

00:25:28.646 --> 00:25:30.876 A:middle
The category requires
a unique identifier.

00:25:31.776 --> 00:25:33.976 A:middle
You give it all the
actions you want.

00:25:34.296 --> 00:25:37.316 A:middle
You can also provide now
some intent identifiers,

00:25:38.786 --> 00:25:40.676 A:middle
for more information
about intents,

00:25:41.436 --> 00:25:43.506 A:middle
you can attend the
Introducing SiriKit Session.

00:25:44.616 --> 00:25:45.876 A:middle
There are also some options

00:25:45.876 --> 00:25:47.376 A:middle
that you can provide
for the category.

00:25:47.956 --> 00:25:50.116 A:middle
We will talk about one
of them in a few moments.

00:25:52.216 --> 00:25:54.096 A:middle
Now, once you've
created all your actions

00:25:54.096 --> 00:25:57.106 A:middle
and all your categories, the
only thing you need to do is

00:25:57.106 --> 00:25:57.886 A:middle
to register them

00:25:58.156 --> 00:26:01.786 A:middle
to the UNUserNotificationCenter
object associated

00:25:58.156 --> 00:26:01.786 A:middle
to the UNUserNotificationCenter
object associated

00:26:01.786 --> 00:26:04.846 A:middle
with your application.

00:26:05.006 --> 00:26:07.446 A:middle
Now let's talk about how you
can present these custom actions

00:26:07.446 --> 00:26:07.966 A:middle
to your user.

00:26:09.096 --> 00:26:12.506 A:middle
You can do so from both remote
and local notifications.

00:26:14.556 --> 00:26:16.766 A:middle
So first for remote
notifications,

00:26:17.276 --> 00:26:20.646 A:middle
the only thing you need to do
is to set a category identifier

00:26:20.646 --> 00:26:24.336 A:middle
in the APS dictionary of the
remote notification payload.

00:26:25.226 --> 00:26:28.536 A:middle
Now this identifier needs to
match one of the identifiers

00:26:28.696 --> 00:26:30.886 A:middle
for the categories you
previously registered.

00:26:33.666 --> 00:26:36.356 A:middle
For local notifications
you just need

00:26:36.356 --> 00:26:37.936 A:middle
to set the category identifier

00:26:38.406 --> 00:26:40.816 A:middle
on the mutable content
that you created.

00:26:41.326 --> 00:26:44.346 A:middle
Same thing this identifier
needs to match the identifier

00:26:44.346 --> 00:26:49.306 A:middle
that you [inaudible] before.

00:26:49.546 --> 00:26:51.146 A:middle
Now let's talk about
the third type of action

00:26:51.146 --> 00:26:53.376 A:middle
that your app can be aware
of is the dismiss action.

00:26:53.906 --> 00:26:58.116 A:middle
Now the dismiss action
is new to iOS X and it is

00:26:58.116 --> 00:27:00.706 A:middle
when the user dismisses
a specific notification.

00:26:58.116 --> 00:27:00.706 A:middle
when the user dismisses
a specific notification.

00:27:02.206 --> 00:27:04.326 A:middle
You could use this
if, for example,

00:27:04.326 --> 00:27:05.946 A:middle
you have a calendar application

00:27:06.596 --> 00:27:09.316 A:middle
and let's say you send a remote
notification to your user

00:27:09.316 --> 00:27:11.236 A:middle
about an upcoming meeting.

00:27:11.996 --> 00:27:13.546 A:middle
The user looks at
the notification

00:27:13.546 --> 00:27:16.726 A:middle
and decides to dismiss it.

00:27:16.986 --> 00:27:18.746 A:middle
When in this case you might want

00:27:18.746 --> 00:27:21.836 A:middle
to stop sending other remote
notifications to other devices

00:27:21.836 --> 00:27:24.206 A:middle
of this user since they have
seen the notification already.

00:27:25.966 --> 00:27:29.026 A:middle
Now, how can the user actually
dismiss the notification?

00:27:29.916 --> 00:27:32.986 A:middle
Well they can do that on
the lock screen by swiping

00:27:32.986 --> 00:27:36.036 A:middle
from right to left, and
tapping on the Clear button.

00:27:38.776 --> 00:27:42.296 A:middle
They can also do that from the
Notification Center by swiping

00:27:42.296 --> 00:27:45.016 A:middle
from right to left as well,
and taping on the Clear button

00:27:45.016 --> 00:27:46.726 A:middle
which will dismiss
the notification.

00:27:50.096 --> 00:27:53.096 A:middle
Now since this is not the
common case you will need

00:27:53.096 --> 00:27:56.076 A:middle
to update for it.

00:27:56.336 --> 00:27:57.646 A:middle
So remember earlier
when we talked

00:27:57.646 --> 00:27:59.706 A:middle
about the different categories
that you could register,

00:28:00.386 --> 00:28:02.576 A:middle
we talked about some
options, this is one of them,

00:28:02.936 --> 00:28:04.516 A:middle
the customDismissAction option.

00:28:05.116 --> 00:28:09.556 A:middle
So let's look at the
code we used earlier

00:28:09.556 --> 00:28:10.776 A:middle
to register our category.

00:28:11.736 --> 00:28:12.876 A:middle
The only thing you
need to do here,

00:28:14.126 --> 00:28:15.946 A:middle
is simply add the
customDismissAction

00:28:16.396 --> 00:28:17.816 A:middle
to the options of this category

00:28:18.196 --> 00:28:20.436 A:middle
and your app will
receive the actions

00:28:20.436 --> 00:28:22.806 A:middle
when the result dismisses
specific notification

00:28:23.136 --> 00:28:23.846 A:middle
with this category.

00:28:27.096 --> 00:28:29.506 A:middle
So let's summarize the actions
that we talked about today.

00:28:30.926 --> 00:28:32.476 A:middle
The first one is
a default action,

00:28:32.876 --> 00:28:34.686 A:middle
when the user opens
your application

00:28:34.866 --> 00:28:35.866 A:middle
from the notification.

00:28:37.636 --> 00:28:39.626 A:middle
The second one where
the custom actions

00:28:39.626 --> 00:28:42.546 A:middle
within actionable notifications
to provide a quick way

00:28:42.546 --> 00:28:45.186 A:middle
for the user to execute
an action directly

00:28:45.186 --> 00:28:46.106 A:middle
from the notification.

00:28:46.626 --> 00:28:50.156 A:middle
And finally the third one
is the dismiss action,

00:28:50.936 --> 00:28:53.466 A:middle
it is new to iOS X and
it allows you to know

00:28:53.506 --> 00:28:56.066 A:middle
when a user dismisses a
specific notification.

00:28:58.516 --> 00:29:03.936 A:middle
