00:29:04.436 --> 00:29:07.446 A:middle
Now let's talk about how you can
actually handle the responses

00:29:07.446 --> 00:29:10.266 A:middle
from these actions
in your application.

00:29:11.546 --> 00:29:13.986 A:middle
So until now we had
several methods based

00:29:13.986 --> 00:29:16.476 A:middle
on if the user opened the
app from a notification,

00:29:16.906 --> 00:29:21.676 A:middle
or if we had custom actions or
text input actions, or if it was

00:29:21.676 --> 00:29:23.456 A:middle
from a remote or a
local notification.

00:29:24.466 --> 00:29:26.956 A:middle
Well now with our new user
notifications framework,

00:29:26.956 --> 00:29:31.956 A:middle
we have a single method
to do that and it is part

00:29:31.956 --> 00:29:35.216 A:middle
of the UNUserNotificationCenter
delegate protocol.

00:29:36.936 --> 00:29:40.686 A:middle
The method you will need to
implement is didReceive response

00:29:40.766 --> 00:29:41.706 A:middle
with CompletionHandler.

00:29:43.886 --> 00:29:46.376 A:middle
Now let's take a closer
look at the response object

00:29:46.376 --> 00:29:48.636 A:middle
and what you can do with
it in your application.

00:29:50.886 --> 00:29:53.426 A:middle
Your response object has
an action identifier,

00:29:53.926 --> 00:29:57.196 A:middle
which can either be the
default, the dismiss action,

00:29:57.586 --> 00:29:59.756 A:middle
or any of the custom
actions that you created.

00:30:01.416 --> 00:30:03.536 A:middle
It can have a user
text property in case

00:30:03.536 --> 00:30:05.406 A:middle
if it was a text input action.

00:30:05.786 --> 00:30:11.096 A:middle
It can also have a notification
object with the request object

00:30:11.096 --> 00:30:14.056 A:middle
and the identifier of
the notification as well

00:30:14.056 --> 00:30:15.196 A:middle
as the trigger and the content.

00:30:16.166 --> 00:30:18.996 A:middle
Based on the type of trigger
you can figure out if it was

00:30:18.996 --> 00:30:21.246 A:middle
from a local or a
remote notification.

00:30:21.776 --> 00:30:24.946 A:middle
So this is all with the new
user notification framework,

00:30:25.336 --> 00:30:27.426 A:middle
you can handle your
responses of actions.

00:30:30.796 --> 00:30:32.626 A:middle
Now, let's talk about
remote notifications.

00:30:33.126 --> 00:30:37.596 A:middle
This is your current
workflow, the workflow

00:30:37.596 --> 00:30:40.146 A:middle
with remote notification that
we saw earlier in this session.

00:30:41.216 --> 00:30:42.676 A:middle
You have your service
identification,

00:30:43.176 --> 00:30:45.366 A:middle
which sends a remote
notification to payload

00:30:45.366 --> 00:30:47.036 A:middle
to Apple push notification
service.

00:30:47.806 --> 00:30:52.266 A:middle
And then it is delivered to the
device and shown to the user.

00:30:52.436 --> 00:30:54.856 A:middle
Now, maybe some of
you are in a situation

00:30:54.856 --> 00:30:58.566 A:middle
where you have your server side
application and you communicate

00:30:58.856 --> 00:31:01.706 A:middle
to your iOS application
maybe using some

00:30:58.856 --> 00:31:01.706 A:middle
to your iOS application
maybe using some

00:31:01.706 --> 00:31:02.746 A:middle
end-to-end encryption.

00:31:04.426 --> 00:31:07.626 A:middle
Well, wouldn't that be great
if you could use that same end

00:31:07.626 --> 00:31:10.836 A:middle
to end encryption for your
remote notification as well?

00:31:13.186 --> 00:31:16.046 A:middle
Well for that in iOS X
we are introducing the

00:31:16.046 --> 00:31:16.966 A:middle
service extension.

00:31:18.316 --> 00:31:19.246 A:middle
So now we are going to talk

00:31:19.246 --> 00:31:21.276 A:middle
about what the service
extension is

00:31:22.006 --> 00:31:23.646 A:middle
and then how you can
actually implement it

00:31:23.646 --> 00:31:24.456 A:middle
in your application.

00:31:28.316 --> 00:31:32.156 A:middle
Now the service extension is
a non iOS extension available

00:31:32.156 --> 00:31:35.296 A:middle
on iOS X, which means it
runs in the background.

00:31:36.476 --> 00:31:41.316 A:middle
And its main purpose is to
augment or replace the content

00:31:41.466 --> 00:31:44.096 A:middle
of visible or remote
notifications before they are

00:31:44.096 --> 00:31:45.016 A:middle
displayed to the user.

00:31:46.926 --> 00:31:49.296 A:middle
So let's take a look again
at your current workflow

00:31:49.296 --> 00:31:50.346 A:middle
for remote notifications.

00:31:50.346 --> 00:31:55.056 A:middle
So you have your server-side
application, you send a payload

00:31:55.056 --> 00:31:56.906 A:middle
to Apple push notification
service

00:31:56.906 --> 00:31:58.486 A:middle
and then it is sent
to the device.

00:32:00.186 --> 00:32:02.016 A:middle
Well, now with the extension,

00:32:02.676 --> 00:32:04.186 A:middle
you're able to modify
the content

00:32:04.666 --> 00:32:05.816 A:middle
between the time you sent it

00:32:05.816 --> 00:32:07.896 A:middle
from your server-side
application

00:32:07.976 --> 00:32:10.446 A:middle
and the time it is displayed
to the user on their device.

00:32:11.326 --> 00:32:14.486 A:middle
As you can see in this
example, I did a title,

00:32:14.486 --> 00:32:15.786 A:middle
as well as a subtitle,

00:32:16.276 --> 00:32:18.426 A:middle
and I modified the body
of the notification.

00:32:21.076 --> 00:32:23.766 A:middle
Now a few more details about
that service extension.

00:32:24.086 --> 00:32:26.816 A:middle
You will get a short execution
time, which means this is not

00:32:26.816 --> 00:32:28.746 A:middle
for long background
running tasks.

00:32:30.466 --> 00:32:34.936 A:middle
And in case you fail to
provide some updated content

00:32:34.936 --> 00:32:37.446 A:middle
in a timely manner, you
will get a fallback method.

00:32:38.546 --> 00:32:40.756 A:middle
In case you still fail to
provide some updated content,

00:32:41.226 --> 00:32:43.806 A:middle
we will show the original
remote notification

00:32:44.016 --> 00:32:45.456 A:middle
that you sent to the user.

00:32:47.336 --> 00:32:50.526 A:middle
Now some potential uses of
that you could use end-to-end

00:32:50.526 --> 00:32:54.636 A:middle
encryption for your remote
notifications and you could

00:32:54.636 --> 00:32:57.836 A:middle
as well add some attachments
to your remote notifications

00:32:57.836 --> 00:32:59.166 A:middle
to make them even richer.

00:33:00.596 --> 00:33:02.786 A:middle
Now there will be a
detailed example on how to do

00:33:02.786 --> 00:33:05.066 A:middle
that in the Advance
Notification Session.

00:33:07.636 --> 00:33:10.526 A:middle
Now let's talk about how you
can actually implement this new

00:33:10.526 --> 00:33:12.446 A:middle
service extension
in your application.

00:33:14.536 --> 00:33:17.666 A:middle
The first thing you would need
to do in your Xcode project

00:33:18.156 --> 00:33:19.066 A:middle
to add the new target.

00:33:19.966 --> 00:33:22.446 A:middle
You can use the template,
which is located

00:33:22.446 --> 00:33:24.866 A:middle
under the application
extension section.

00:33:25.856 --> 00:33:27.866 A:middle
And it is known as the
notification service.

00:33:28.726 --> 00:33:31.536 A:middle
Now this template
has one main class.

00:33:32.656 --> 00:33:37.846 A:middle
So we are going to take a look
at a simplified version of it.

00:33:38.106 --> 00:33:41.076 A:middle
So this class, is a subclass

00:33:41.076 --> 00:33:43.276 A:middle
of the UNNotification
service extension

00:33:44.556 --> 00:33:45.706 A:middle
and it has two main methods.

00:33:48.246 --> 00:33:52.056 A:middle
The first method is
didReceive with ContentHandler.

00:33:53.676 --> 00:33:56.296 A:middle
Now this method will give
you the current request

00:33:56.296 --> 00:33:58.366 A:middle
which has the identifier
for the notification

00:33:58.646 --> 00:33:59.626 A:middle
as well as the content.

00:34:00.936 --> 00:34:02.506 A:middle
Then we have the ContentHandler.

00:34:03.016 --> 00:34:05.876 A:middle
You will need to call this
ContentHandler when you want

00:34:05.876 --> 00:34:08.386 A:middle
to present the notification
to your user, and you need

00:34:08.386 --> 00:34:12.505 A:middle
to provide some content for it.

00:34:12.775 --> 00:34:15.775 A:middle
Now, the second method is
service extension time will

00:34:15.775 --> 00:34:17.795 A:middle
expire, and this will be called

00:34:17.795 --> 00:34:20.585 A:middle
if you cannot provide updated
content in a timely manner.

00:34:21.976 --> 00:34:25.366 A:middle
So now remember if you fail
to call the ContentHandler

00:34:25.366 --> 00:34:28.996 A:middle
in this method, we will show
the original remote notification

00:34:28.996 --> 00:34:30.156 A:middle
content that you sent.

00:34:33.525 --> 00:34:36.565 A:middle
So now let's talk about how you
can actually trigger this code

00:34:36.565 --> 00:34:38.085 A:middle
from a remote notification.

00:34:41.676 --> 00:34:43.706 A:middle
Here, we have a very
simple example

00:34:43.706 --> 00:34:46.056 A:middle
of remote notification
payload with an alert.

00:34:47.126 --> 00:34:50.696 A:middle
And as you can see we have a new
key, the mutable content key.

00:34:51.716 --> 00:34:54.255 A:middle
Now, you will need to use this
key to let the system know

00:34:54.496 --> 00:34:56.356 A:middle
that you want the service
extension to be launched

00:34:56.856 --> 00:34:58.856 A:middle
to update the remote
notification content.

00:35:00.476 --> 00:35:02.766 A:middle
You do not need to use
this key every time,

00:35:03.016 --> 00:35:04.656 A:middle
only use it when
you actually want

00:35:04.656 --> 00:35:06.546 A:middle
to replace the content
of the notification.

00:35:10.046 --> 00:35:12.756 A:middle
Now you can see that I also
added some encrypted content

00:35:12.756 --> 00:35:13.366 A:middle
of my own.

00:35:14.036 --> 00:35:16.246 A:middle
So let's take a look at some
code, which will be able

00:35:16.246 --> 00:35:18.696 A:middle
to process this remote
notification payload.

00:35:22.276 --> 00:35:25.916 A:middle
So you can see here we have
our didReceive( request method,

00:35:25.916 --> 00:35:30.336 A:middle
and the first thing I do here is
I decrypt the encrypted content

00:35:30.416 --> 00:35:31.956 A:middle
of the remote notification
payload.

00:35:35.356 --> 00:35:38.046 A:middle
I then create a
MutableNotificationContent

00:35:38.226 --> 00:35:43.056 A:middle
object and I assign the
body of this notification

00:35:43.626 --> 00:35:46.176 A:middle
